Air Liquide, BP, Imperial Tobacco: European Equity Preview

-- B y   K a i t l y n   K i e r n a n
-- 
2011-12-02T05:00:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-01/air-liquide-bp-imperial-tobacco-european-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
have unusual moves in  European  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  The  Stoxx Europe 600 Index  lost 0.7 percent to 238.49. The
 Stoxx 50 Index  fell 0.5 percent to 2,287.12. The  Euro Stoxx 50
Index (SX5E) , a benchmark measure for nations using the euro, slipped
0.7 percent to 2,313.84.  Air Liquide SA (AI)  : The industrial gas producer was cut
to “sell” from “hold” at Hamburger Sparkasse. The shares
lost 2.1 percent to 91.95 euros.  BP Plc  (BP/ LN):  Europe ’s second-biggest oil company agreed
to sell its Canadian gas-liquids operations to  Plains All
American Pipeline LP (PAA)   for $1.67 billion in cash. BP
shares fell 1.4 percent to 454.35 pence in  London . Plains rose
1.7 percent to $65.98 in  New York .  Imperial Tobacco Group (IMT)  : Europe’s second-biggest
tobacco company will replace  AXA SA (CS)  , the continent’s
second-largest insurer, in the Stoxx Europe 50 Index and the
Stoxx Global 150 Index, Stoxx Ltd. said in an e-mailed
statement. The changes will be effective at the open of  European (SXXP) 
markets on Dec. 19.  Imperial Tobacco  shares advanced 1 percent
to 2,310 pence. AXA shares fell 2.1 percent to 10.50 euros.  Neopost SA (NEO)  : The supplier of mailroom equipment
said third-quarter revenue rose 3.6 percent to 242 million
euros. The Bagneux, France-based company narrowed its full-year
sales growth forecast to 4.5 percent to 5.5 percent, from 4
percent to 6 percent earlier. The shares fell 2 percent to 51.56
euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
